{"word":"G395 - ἀνατολή - anatolḗ - an-at-ol-ay' - Dayspring","slug":"G395","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀνατολή</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>anatolḗ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>an-at-ol-ay'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Dayspring"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B1;&#x0313;&#x03BD;&#x03B1;&#x03C4;&#x03BF;&#x03BB;&#x03B7;&#x0301; - anatole&#x0304;</b> - <i>an-at-ol-ay'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G393\">G393</a>; a <i>rising</i> of light, that is, <i>dawn</i> (figuratively); by implication the <i>east</i> (also in plural): - dayspring, east, rising."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G393\">G393</a>"}]}